\section abstract Abstract

%GeographicLib is a small set of <a href="annotated.html">C++
classes</a> for performing conversions between geographic, UTM, UPS,
MGRS, geocentric, and local cartesian coordinates and for solving
geodesic problems.  The emphasis is on returning accurate results with
errors close to round-off (about 5&ndash;15 nm).  In addition, various
properties of the \ref transversemercator are described and an accurate
algorithm for \ref geodesic is given.

