z[6] = + 77/2048 * k1^6
       + 33/4096 * k1^8;
z[7] = + 429/14336 * k1^7;
z[8] = + 6435/262144 * k1^8;
\endverbatim

The longitude is given in terms of the spherical longitude by

&nbsp; &nbsp;
\e lambda - \e chi = sin \e alpha<sub>0</sub> \e H \e eta(\e sigma)

where

&nbsp; &nbsp; \e eta(\e sigma) =
